1
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:10,800
The printer is broken.

2
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,000
I sent print jobs but nothing came out.

3
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,120
I already called a repairman.

4
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:14,800
His name is Boom.

5
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,680
Please check the printer...

6
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:18,480
What’s wrong with your tongue?

7
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:23,480
If your mouth is too tight, then don’t talk.

8
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:26,480
This is the new fish.
Shouldn’t we give a welcome?

9
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:27,560
No!

10
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:30,080
My eyes are burning, Sergeant.

11
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:31,760
I am not a sergeant.

12
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:34,600
I am Inspector Akkarin Thanapuwadech.

13
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:35,920
I was framed.

14
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:37,000
I will listen to you.

15
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,000
But please make sure it is the truth.

16
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:48,320
I never thought you’d dare do this to us.

17
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:52,480
Do you know how much Glamorous will suffer because of you alone?

18
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:55,560
Look at you, still calm?

19
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,520
I don’t think talking nicely will work anymore, Sky.

20
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:58,520
Go ahead.

21
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:00,840
Do you regret it now?

22
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Silent? You’re still silent, huh?

23
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:08,360
So you still don’t regret it, do you?

24
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:12,400
Wait, are you guys ganging up on the printer?

25
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:16,480
They say if you smack appliances, they’ll start working again.

26
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:19,880
I sent print jobs but nothing came out. I’ll…

27
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:22,400
That’s enough.

28
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,280
Why not let All-New fix it?

29
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,280
All-New?

30
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:28,000
Look at your friend’s condition first.

31
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:31,880
Even more broken than the printer.

32
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,560
Do you know what he’s been through?

33
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,280
Why is he like that?

34
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:35,680
He doesn’t move at all.

35
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:37,080
And he’s covered in cobwebs.

36
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,440
I’ve seen him standing still like that since yesterday.

37
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:43,400
Back when we were talking about Madam Porn getting arrested.

38
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:47,400
So what does All-New have to do with Madam Porn?

39
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:49,800
Maybe he’s just too lazy to walk.

40
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:53,000
Well, that makes sense.

41
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Wait, does it?

42
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,360
Oh!

43
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:59,200
The repairman’s here.

44
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:02,000
Repairman? Repair what?

45
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,680
Well, repair the printer!

46
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:07,160
What? You called a repairman and didn’t tell me?

47
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:09,320
You let me smash the printer till my hand’s almost broken.

48
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:11,280
I thought you were just playing around.

49
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,360
Just for fun, you know.

50
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,680
Like Toey and Bee in Hormones.

51
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:15,840
I'll go pick him up first, okay?

52
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:18,440
And if the repairman’s useless,

53
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:20,240
I won’t talk to you anymore, Chaba.

54
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:25,280
Here we are, here he is!

55
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:34,720
This is Boom, the repairman.

56
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:55,560
Oh wow, Chaba, he’s got a "hottie" tattoo.

57
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:59,440
I call dibs on him.

58
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:05,240
Please take a look at the...

59
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,720
The what?

60
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,720
What’s wrong with your tongue?

61
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:13,560
Did too much MSG make it swell or what?

62
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:16,560
If your mouth’s too tight, then don’t talk.

63
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:18,400
Well? Hot enough for you?

64
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:21,400
Move aside, Plain-face.

65
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:22,400
Plain-face...

66
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,800
Plain-face!

67
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,280
Just turn the printer off and on.

68
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:28,760
That’s it?

69
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:29,920
Then fix it yourself.

70
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,720
Uh, well…

71
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:35,440
You don’t know how to fix it but you want to teach the repair guy?

72
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:37,320
Did you try turning it off?

73
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,320
Try.

74
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:44,120
It...it didn’t work.

75
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:48,280
See?

76
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:49,960
Did it work?

77
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:50,800
Uh...

78
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,640
Did it work? I asked, did it work?

79
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:53,280
Yes, it did.

80
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:56,720
See? Just that.
Turn it off and on, and it works, idiot.

81
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:59,880
What have you even done with your life?
You don’t even know how to restart a printer...

82
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:02,400
Should I smack you instead?

83
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,320
Chaba.

84
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:03,960
Yes?

85
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:05,200
Aren’t you gonna say anything?

86
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,000
What do you want me to say?

87
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,200
If I say anything, he’ll just call me fat.

88
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:08,720
Barrel.

89
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,800
Huh?

90
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:10,640
Stamp the card.

91
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:12,000
A barrel can be tiny too...

92
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,400
Well, at least barrel is better than fat.

93
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,720
Glasses.

94
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:18,040
Glasses.

95
00:05:19,880 --> 00:05:21,240
What are you doing just standing there?

96
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,080
Even standing still gets you roasted.

97
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:24,360
Barrel, what are you mumbling?

98
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,440
Nothing.

99
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:26,880
Stamp the card and finish quickly. Go.

100
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:27,760
Alright.

101
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:28,320
This is such a waste of time.

102
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:30,520
Come on, let’s go home, repairman.

103
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:31,680
Everyone’s hurt already, let’s go.

104
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,680
This way, please.

105
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,280
Damn printer!

106
00:05:36,280 --> 00:05:37,960
After all that, it didn’t work.

107
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:41,000
Just Boom showing up and suddenly it worked.

108
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,240
Kreetha, come help me print this.

109
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,880
Kreetha...

110
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,200
It wouldn't turn off.

111
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,080
What’s wrong?

112
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:50,040
It just wouldn’t turn off, what do you want me to do?
It wouldn't turn off.

113
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,160
What’s going on here?

114
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:54,400
Is this an airline office or a mental hospital?

115
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,920
Well, since we’re here anyway,

116
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:57,240
I’ll just start dancing.

117
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:58,240
Come on.

118
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,680
Let’s have a contest.

119
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,960
I couldn’t turn it off.

120
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:05,240
Come on!

121
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:06,640
Since we’re all crazy already, let's do it!

122
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,120
Siri,

123
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,800
stop crying already.

124
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:26,960
Why don’t you look worried at all, Madam?

125
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:29,320
Because of Glam, that’s why.

126
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,520
So, is Glam here to help us, Madam?

127
00:06:31,520 --> 00:06:33,120
Ugh, are you crazy?

128
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:36,280
I know the reason we’re stuck here...

129
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:38,640
is all Glam’s doing.

130
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,600
Hey!

131
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:42,640
If anyone benefits from this, it’s only him.

132
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:45,640
And no one else hates me enough to pull this off.

133
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:49,560
Well, the part about benefits, I get that, Madam.

134
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:52,880
But the part about hating you, that’s not so certain.
You do have plenty.

135
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:53,880
Siri!

136
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,600
Quiet, girl.

137
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,680
Girl?

138
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,200
Who are you calling girl, old hag?

139
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:06,200
And who are you calling old hag?

140
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:10,720
Oh, it's the new fish.

141
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:13,040
Shouldn’t we give a welcome?

142
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:15,200
No need. Thanks.

143
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,800
I didn’t give you a choice.

144
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,800
It’s an order. Hey!

145
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:20,880
Hey!

146
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:22,840
Wait! What are you doing?

147
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,400
Just doing...

148
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,400
Where’s the female prisoner, Madam Porn?

149
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:30,280
Oh, don’t be scared, dear.
Mommy will take care of you.

150
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:32,880
She’s just new here, of course she’s scared.

151
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:34,840
So we’re just trying to comfort her a bit.

152
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:36,840
Scared of you, more like...

153
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:40,040
Save the comforting for later.
Come out here first.

154
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:47,280
So I finally get to go out, right? At last...

155
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,880
You’re going out for more questioning.

156
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:50,880
Oh.

157
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:54,640
Well, at least you still get to be with the police, Madam.

158
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:57,200
Better than being stuck with them.

159
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,680
What’s wrong with "them"?

160
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:01,040
All they’re good at is trash-talking behind your back.

161
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:03,080
But when the real deal shows up, they shrink.

162
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:05,360
If you’re so tough, do the hazing in front of the cops.

163
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:16,360
Only Madam Porn is coming.
The rest of you stay here.

164
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:22,640
Who just said we only act tough behind people’s backs?

165
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:27,400
Well, the cops turned around,
so let me show you some toughness right to your face.

166
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:38,720
No!

167
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:45,080
No!

168
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:47,080
Oh, it's not sour!

169
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,720
Here, eat, eat.

170
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:55,200
Oh, it's only a snack. Thank God.

171
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:56,880
It's no good!

172
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,040
Gift!

173
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:10,160
Tid-Gift!

174
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:14,840
Gift!

175
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,400
What? You scared me!

176
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,920
You’re too busy chasing guys,
you can’t even hear your friend calling.

177
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:22,040
Ugh, the AC’s so loud, I couldn’t hear.

178
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:23,800
The AC hums, sure.

179
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:27,160
But Sky’s voice is booming,
I can hear it from here.

180
00:09:27,160 --> 00:09:29,240
If you’re not boy-crazy,
what else should we call you, Tid-Gift?

181
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:33,720
Oh, come on, it’s not every day I match with a cute guy.

182
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:37,640
Polite, gentle, soft, sweet...

183
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:39,400
Can’t I swoon for a moment?

184
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,560
Mm.

185
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:42,160
So why were you calling me, Sky?

186
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:43,960
Have you seen Chai?

187
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,480
I only saw Dohee.

188
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:49,960
Ooh, Dohee.

189
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,960
Korean guy?

190
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:56,920
Scratch if you itch.
Don’t go prowling around for men.

191
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:00,800
And where’s Chai that you saw?
Answer.

192
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,800
He said he was going to find the air-con repairman.

193
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:08,960
Sky, the printer’s jammed again.

194
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:09,880
Should I call Boom?

195
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:12,400
Don’t you dare call Boom again.

196
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:15,240
Change to someone else.
You just keep writing those instead.

197
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,640
I need a thousand copies printed.

198
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:20,080
Then you hand-write a thousand,
no need to call him again.

199
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,080
Boom who?

200
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:23,680
It’s hot.

201
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,200
Hello, Chai.

202
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,840
Should I send the meeting minutes today?

203
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,160
If it’s done, send it in.

204
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:33,160
Okay.

205
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,320
But you look fresh today.

206
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:42,160
The printer’s broken, and it’s boiling hot,

207
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:43,520
I’m sweating all over.

208
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:45,560
I already called the air-con repairman.

209
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:49,120
But today, please take care of him, I’ve got errands.

210
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,720
Perfect timing. When will he be here?

211
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:52,280
Maybe in about an hour.

212
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:54,960
Ugh, can’t he come sooner?
I’m roasting.

213
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:57,360
Stop fussing.
He’ll be here soon.

214
00:10:58,040 --> 00:10:59,960
By the way, the repairmsn's name is cute.

215
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:00,800
His name is Boom.

216
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:03,120
Huh?

217
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,640
Boom, the repairman?

218
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:07,800
Yeah, Boom.

219
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:11,120
What’s with you guys?

220
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:12,800
Anyway, I’m off now.

221
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,440
Hey, I’m doomed.

222
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,320
We're gonna get hurt again.

223
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:19,320
Barrel!

224
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,480
What? What’s wrong with you two?

225
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:22,480
Who the hell is Boom?

226
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,400
Dohee...

227
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:38,240
I already told you I didn’t do it.
I’m being framed.

228
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,240
Who?

229
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,360
It's Glam, the owner of Glamorous Airline.

230
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,680
What about evidence?

231
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:46,360
They brought me in like this...
how could there be any evidence?

232
00:11:46,360 --> 00:11:49,120
Then let me go so I can find more evidence.

233
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:50,360
Stay calm.

234
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:53,560
Oh, this is blinding, can you turn off the lights first?

235
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:55,400
For someone like you, this is still too little.

236
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:57,320
Why? Why me?

237
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:59,840
My eyes are burning, Sergeant.
Try it for yourself!

238
00:12:02,920 --> 00:12:04,120
So handsome...

239
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,280
I’m not a sergeant.

240
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:10,960
I am Inspector Akkarin Thanapuwadech.

241
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:21,320
Inspector Akkarin, please turn the light on, my eyes hurt.

242
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:28,080
Akkarin Thanapuwadech.

243
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:30,040
Do I have to say both your first and last name?

244
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,840
No need, just the first name is fine...

245
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:35,880
Which is Akkarin Thanapuwadech.

246
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:39,840
Okay, Inspector Akkarin Thanapubech.

247
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:40,760
Puwadech...

248
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:47,200
Inspector, I didn’t do it, alright?

249
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:52,240
No!

250
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:55,360
What’s this? It's evidence.

251
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:57,960
All the evidence points to you.

252
00:12:57,960 --> 00:13:00,960
You have no way out.

253
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:02,960
Even when stern, he’s still handsome.

254
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,360
That’s not true.

255
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:08,520
Today I’m only here to hear a confession.

256
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:10,000
But I didn’t...

257
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,440
Confess!

258
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:37,440
What should I do?
Guys like this never listen to anything, except...

259
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:46,080
I don’t have all day, you know.

260
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:50,040
Why are you crying?

261
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:55,240
Honestly, a hundred percent of men melt at a woman’s tears.

262
00:13:57,760 --> 00:13:59,520
I’m not crying.

263
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:02,200
Not crying? Here’s the evidence!

264
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:05,600
Why do you always give testimony that contradicts the evidence?

265
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,480
Evidence, evidence...

266
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:11,440
You! You only talk about evidence!
You never listen to me!

267
