498
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:06,360
Liar! The pulse says so.

499
00:27:06,360 --> 00:27:08,760
Pulse tests can make mistakes, right?

500
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:10,080
Yeah, true.

501
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:11,080
Then allow me.

502
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:19,560
Are you okay?

503
00:27:19,560 --> 00:27:21,840
Your pulse is irregular, really strong.

504
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:27,840
Oh, can we use another method?

505
00:27:28,240 --> 00:27:32,240
Why? Are you afraid I’ll detect something?
You’ve got suspicious signs.

506
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:35,480
What suspicious signs?
Are you crazy?

507
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:36,600
Are you hiding something?

508
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:39,040
I told you, there’s nothing.

509
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:39,920
Wait!

510
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:40,400
Hey.

511
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:41,400
Stop!

512
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:01,680
What? What are you doing?

513
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:06,440
Oh my, what are you doing?

514
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:10,440
We’ll wait until your pulse returns to normal
before we continue questioning.

515
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:17,960
It’s already been an hour...

516
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:19,960
and your pulse is still weird.

517
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,600
Thank you so much.

518
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:46,000
Japan-Korea beauty, all at Found & Found.

519
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:50,960
Shop tons of Japanese and Korean beauty products
without flying or pre-ordering.

520
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:53,680
Oh nice! No flying, no waiting for pre-orders.

521
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:56,160
Feels like walking in a Korean store, girl.

522
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:01,480
Sky, Chaba, I’m excited.

523
00:29:03,040 --> 00:29:05,880
Like you’ve never met someone from an app before.

524
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:10,280
But this is my first time seeing Dohee in person.

525
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:12,080
And his profile pic...?

526
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:14,040
He doesn't use his real photo.

527
00:29:14,040 --> 00:29:16,600
Huh, and have you sent photos to each other before?

528
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:18,440
He’s shy.

529
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:19,920
He might be a scammer.

530
00:29:20,600 --> 00:29:21,920
Nope.

531
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:24,040
I bet he’s ugly as hell.

532
00:29:24,040 --> 00:29:25,720
Yeah, totally possible.

533
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:30,640
But seriously, I felt connected to him when we talked.

534
00:29:30,960 --> 00:29:34,520
I wouldn’t care if he was...shit!

535
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:40,920
I can picture it already.

536
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:44,120
It's not that! I ran into that repair guy, Boom.

537
00:29:44,120 --> 00:29:45,480
What do I do?

538
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:47,600
If he walks by, I’ll definitely snap at him.

539
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:50,360
And if Dohee sees me yelling,

540
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:52,520
he’ll run away for sure.

541
00:29:52,520 --> 00:29:54,520
Then, go somewhere else.

542
00:29:54,520 --> 00:29:56,800
What if Dohee can’t find me?

543
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:58,400
Then kick Boom out.

544
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:01,400
Or just insult him, you’ll win for sure.

545
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:03,800
Okay, okay, got it.

546
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:10,040
Hey, air attendant, what are you doing?

547
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:13,440
Nosy, right?

548
00:30:14,160 --> 00:30:15,280
You wanted to say that, right?

549
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:20,120
Smart move, but want to be smarter?

550
00:30:20,960 --> 00:30:22,160
How?

551
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:23,720
Get far away from here!

552
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:26,800
Okay, then...

553
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,160
As if...

554
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:32,440
What?

555
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:34,520
Sitting here is comfy, I’ll stay.

556
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:35,560
What?

557
00:30:35,560 --> 00:30:37,360
Why? Is this your...

558
00:30:37,360 --> 00:30:44,040
This isn’t my dad’s spot or my mom’s, but I want to sit here.

559
00:30:44,040 --> 00:30:46,080
And it’d be so much better

560
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:50,080
if there weren’t assholes like you ruining the mood.

561
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:51,760
So...

562
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:56,280
Thanks.

563
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:09,120
Tid-Gift: Can we move to meet at the parking lot?

564
00:31:09,120 --> 00:31:10,520
Dohee: Okay.

565
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:14,440
If you want to stay here, stay.

566
00:31:15,880 --> 00:31:16,880
What?

567
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:24,360
Tid-Gift: Better to switch back to the original meeting spot.

568
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:29,480
Ugh, what is this?

569
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:30,480
What?

570
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:36,520
Tid-Gift: Change to the parking lot.

571
00:31:41,520 --> 00:31:42,200
Tid-Gift: Wait.

572
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:49,760
What’s her problem?

573
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:57,680
Don’t tell me you're meeting someone from an app.

574
00:31:57,840 --> 00:31:58,840
What?

575
00:31:59,760 --> 00:32:00,760
Thank God.

576
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:04,760
How’d you know?

577
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:11,320
You're Tid-Gif?

578
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:12,520
It’s Tid-Gift, damn it.

579
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:15,440
Why didn't you use your real name?

580
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:18,280
Why fake being Korean as “Dohee”?

581
00:32:18,280 --> 00:32:20,840
Fake what? That is my real name.

582
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:24,560
Listen, Dohee is Deeho.

583
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:27,480
Deeho is Well-ho. Well-ho is Bohho.

584
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:29,040
Bohho is a Bhor-loom.

585
00:32:29,040 --> 00:32:32,800
Bhor-loom is Boom-lhor (handsome Boom).

586
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:35,360
Enough, I don’t want to hear it.

587
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:37,400
Besides being rude,

588
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:39,400
you’re acting psycho.

589
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:41,880
I’m explaining, can’t you understand?

590
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:44,120
Boom-lhor, Bhor-loom.

591
00:32:44,120 --> 00:32:46,800
Bhor is well. Loom is ho.

592
00:32:46,800 --> 00:32:48,160
Dohee, Deeho.

593
00:32:48,160 --> 00:32:51,160
Enough, I don’t get it.
I don’t want to stay here.

594
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:59,000
What’s so hard to understand?
It’s easier than Tid-Gift.

595
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:12,200
Hello, Inspector.

596
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:18,000
Hello, Inspector.

597
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:20,800
Hey, Inspector, hey!

598
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:27,840
Hello, Inspec...

599
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:31,080
Oh! All-New, Kreetha...

600
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:35,440
Hey, All-New, Kreetha, how did you get here?

601
00:33:35,440 --> 00:33:36,920
I told them I’m a lawyer.

602
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:38,280
And they believed you?

603
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:39,560
I have a license.

604
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:42,280
I passed the bar, Madam, don’t you remember?

605
00:33:42,280 --> 00:33:44,880
I’m here to help get you out of here.

606
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:48,160
All-New, you believe me, right? I didn’t do it.

607
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:49,160
Of course.

608
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:53,840
All-New says there’s no way you could have a hundred cases like that.

609
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:55,800
Even if you’ve changed lately…

610
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:56,920
Depraved.

611
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:57,920
Brutal.

612
00:33:57,920 --> 00:33:58,600
Evil.

613
00:33:58,600 --> 00:33:59,560
Inhumane.

614
00:33:59,560 --> 00:34:03,560
Wait, those last ones you added yourself, right?

615
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:05,000
Sorry, Madam.

616
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:10,000
All-New, you’re not mad at me anymore, right?

617
00:34:11,280 --> 00:34:14,720
I get why you’re so vengeful toward Glam now.

618
00:34:14,720 --> 00:34:18,360
Because all of this was his doing, right?

619
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:21,400
Finally, you understand me, at least once.

620
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:22,920
But why did you suddenly believe?

621
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:25,520
Do you remember when Glam sent people to kill us?

622
00:34:25,520 --> 00:34:27,880
I noticed that the cops who arrested you were...

623
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:29,320
one of their people.

624
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:32,320
The police who arrested me?

625
00:34:38,320 --> 00:34:39,920
But that’s just what we saw.

626
00:34:39,920 --> 00:34:42,480
They might have infiltrated more...
We don’t know.

627
00:34:42,480 --> 00:34:44,480
So we must be very careful.

628
00:34:45,640 --> 00:34:47,800
So, Madam, stay here patiently for now.

629
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:50,200
All-New will find a way to get you out.

630
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:51,920
Mm.

631
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:06,800
What’s Chai thinking?

632
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:10,160
Yeah, right. Why all of a sudden suspect All-New?

633
00:35:10,880 --> 00:35:13,080
And now, he even hired someone to hack All-New’s computer.

634
00:35:14,040 --> 00:35:15,960
That’s not the worst part.

635
00:35:15,960 --> 00:35:17,960
Look who he hired,

636
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:22,000
is there only one repair guy in this country?

637
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:24,680
And he can do everything, too.

638
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:28,680
So, did you go on that date yesterday? How was it?

639
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:31,920
There was nothing.

640
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:34,040
That's what I thought, he must be ugly, right?

641
00:35:34,040 --> 00:35:37,040
The face isn’t the problem.
But everything else is fucked.

642
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:41,880
Ugh.

643
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:44,640
Finished hacking already?

644
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:48,000
Nah, I'm going home.
This is impossible.

645
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:50,000
Why?

646
00:35:51,120 --> 00:35:54,680
It's too hard.
That glasses guy locked it with like seventy-eight layers.

647
00:35:54,680 --> 00:35:55,680
This is hopeless.

648
00:35:56,200 --> 00:35:58,200
There’s still time, we can do it slowly.

649
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:04,240
All-New and Kreetha are coming up the elevator now.

650
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:05,240
How long?

651
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:10,040
Two minutes?
I can’t make it, impossible.

652
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:14,040
Twenty thousand baht,
do whatever it takes to learn All-New’s secret.

653
00:36:14,040 --> 00:36:15,040
Why didn’t you say so from the start?

654
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:18,760
But we need a place to do it.

655
00:36:19,040 --> 00:36:19,720
Mm.

656
00:36:19,720 --> 00:36:20,720
Okay.

657
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:26,080
Come in, come in!

658
00:36:26,080 --> 00:36:27,160
To do what?

659
00:36:27,160 --> 00:36:30,200
We’re eavesdropping...
to find out what that glasses guy’s secret is.

660
00:36:30,840 --> 00:36:31,840
Hold on.

661
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:33,840
The room’s full, there’s not enough air.
Go!

662
00:36:34,760 --> 00:36:36,880
What the...always bossing people around.

663
00:36:37,240 --> 00:36:38,240
So annoying.

664
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:40,680
Does this count toward the 20K deal?

665
00:36:50,840 --> 00:36:51,840
What are you going to do about Madam Porn?

666
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:55,440
With so many cases pinned on her,

667
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:56,600
there must be some holes in them.

668
00:36:58,440 --> 00:37:00,840
Hey, I heard him loud and clear.

669
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:07,680
Let’s go to Madam Porn’s office first, then we’ll talk.

670
00:37:07,680 --> 00:37:08,680
Let’s go.

671
00:37:14,960 --> 00:37:16,960
Hey, Chai, did you hear that earlier?

672
00:37:18,600 --> 00:37:22,600
See? All-New and Kreetha are actually involved with Madam Porn.

673
00:37:22,880 --> 00:37:25,600
All-New might be curious about Madam Porn.

674
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:27,800
And just play detective like Conan, that’s all.

675
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:29,160
Then I’ll cosplay as Sherlock Holmes.

676
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:31,280
So I can catch them red-handed.

677
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:32,880
Can I be Robin?

678
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:33,880
Fuck, wrong character...

679
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:39,880
Wait.

680
00:37:39,880 --> 00:37:40,640
Hey, whoa!

681
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:42,840
Wow, rushing off without waiting for me.

682
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:48,280
What are you waiting for?
Waiting for Prince Charming to open it for you?

683
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:57,040
Wait, so the whole office is going? No one’s left?

684
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:59,000
If you’re curious, check for yourself.

685
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:03,000
I’m checking, there really is no one, only the two of us left.

686
00:38:04,560 --> 00:38:10,560
So that means we can date now, right?

687
00:38:11,320 --> 00:38:12,920
Alright, alright.

688
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:16,440
Why do we have to keep our relationship a secret?
Do you have a lot of husbands or what?

689
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:18,400
That’s not it, you, psycho.

690
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:22,000
Isn’t it weird?
We insult each other and then suddenly start dating.

691
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:24,600
Tell others we’re not like other couples.

692
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:26,720
Us fighting is what makes it good.

693
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:29,240
Insult quickly, insult often, insult hard.

694
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:32,200
Enough, enough, that’ll make “that” happen.

695
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:32,920
What’s “that”?

696
00:38:32,920 --> 00:38:33,600
That thing, you know.

697
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:34,400
What is that thing?

698
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:36,840
Hey, enough, go, go, go.

699
00:38:36,840 --> 00:38:37,800
That thing, what is it?

700
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:39,280
Yeah, like that.

701
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:46,920
We need to find anything that can be used as evidence

702
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:51,160
that Madam Porn was framed before the police had found her.

703
00:38:53,800 --> 00:38:54,800
Need any help?

704
00:39:01,080 --> 00:39:02,080
I get it all now.

705
00:39:02,680 --> 00:39:03,680
I can explain.

706
00:39:03,680 --> 00:39:04,680
Everything’s clear now.

707
00:39:05,280 --> 00:39:06,600
Chai, listen to us first.

708
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:07,720
Don’t say anything.

709
00:39:16,120 --> 00:39:18,120
You guys are amazing.

710
00:39:19,600 --> 00:39:20,600
Huh?

711
00:39:21,160 --> 00:39:23,800
At first, I thought you two were Glamorous Airline’s moles.

712
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:26,400
But I didn’t think you two loved Glamorous Airline enough

713
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:28,400
to frame Madam Porn like this.

714
00:39:28,960 --> 00:39:32,080
You two went too far.

715
00:39:32,520 --> 00:39:34,520
You got Madam Porn thrown in jail.

716
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:37,280
You can put it that way...

717
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:40,600
Honestly, it shouldn’t have been done.

718
00:39:40,600 --> 00:39:42,480
Even if Madam Porn is greedy,

719
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:43,280
wicked,

720
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:44,120
evil,

721
00:39:44,120 --> 00:39:45,000
wrinkled,

722
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:46,320
and so old...

723
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:47,320
Hey!

724
00:39:48,880 --> 00:39:49,880
Stop talking shit about my mom!

725
00:39:51,240 --> 00:39:52,840
I meant Madam Porn.

726
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:53,840
That is my mom.

727
00:39:55,160 --> 00:39:57,360
All-New, what the hell are you on about?

728
00:39:57,360 --> 00:39:59,240
Oh, I get it.

729
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:02,320
All-New must feel sorry for Madam Porn, that’s why he said that.

730
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:03,520
Madam Porn really is my mother.

731
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,360
Even if she didn’t give birth to me,

732
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:09,280
she raised me to be who I am today.

733
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:10,800
A lot of words...

734
00:40:10,800 --> 00:40:13,720
Way more meaning than they deserve...

735
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:16,920
Yeah, I think you’re way too into this news, All-New.

736
00:40:17,400 --> 00:40:18,960
Pull yourself together, All-New.
Pull yourself together.

737
00:40:18,960 --> 00:40:19,960
Right.

738
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:21,880
Madam Porn just sent us as spies...

739
00:40:21,880 --> 00:40:23,880
embedded as Glamorous’ flight attendants, right?

740
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:26,760
Oops!

741
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:28,680
Spies for Madam Porn?

742
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:32,000
And Madam Porn is really my mother.

743
00:40:32,560 --> 00:40:33,560
Huh?

744
00:40:44,360 --> 00:40:46,360
And this is the punishment for traitors.

745
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:50,320
Everyone, start!

746
00:40:57,160 --> 00:40:58,160
So, does that hurt?

747
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:01,440
What era are we even in?

748
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:02,480
They deserve it.

749
00:41:02,880 --> 00:41:04,880
For betraying us.

750
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:06,720
Keep throwing.

751
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:09,080
Ouch, ouch!

752
00:41:11,240 --> 00:41:13,480
Getting pelted until you act all girly, huh?

753
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:16,720
It’s too big! It won't fit!

754
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:17,720
Gift!

755
00:41:18,880 --> 00:41:19,720
What are you doing?

756
00:41:19,720 --> 00:41:20,720
And with who?

757
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:24,280
It’s huge, oh! Oh! Oh!

758
00:41:24,280 --> 00:41:26,440
Ahhh, done.

759
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:28,440
Boom!

760
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:32,080
Oh, you’re back already?

761
00:41:32,080 --> 00:41:33,840
We nearly died fixing the printer.

762
00:41:33,840 --> 00:41:37,840
The ink cartridge was massive,
it couldn’t fit it in, my hands are wrecked.

763
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:38,920
Oh.

764
00:41:40,240 --> 00:41:41,240
So why are these two tied up?

765
00:41:42,920 --> 00:41:43,920
They confessed.

766
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:46,680
They said they’re spies from Porn Airline.

767
00:41:46,680 --> 00:41:47,720
Huh?

768
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:48,920
Those two idiots, a fool and glasses?

769
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:50,240
I don’t wear glasses.

770
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:51,560
Not you, you're a fool.

771
00:41:52,200 --> 00:41:53,200
Please let us go.

772
00:41:53,280 --> 00:41:54,840
What I said earlier, I wasn’t in my right mind.

773
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:56,160
Ha, chicken!

774
00:41:56,760 --> 00:42:00,280
Right mind or not, you spoke the truth.

775
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:02,400
You're snakes.

776
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:03,840
Backstabbers.

777
00:42:04,720 --> 00:42:05,720
Thorns in the side.

778
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:10,280
Scammers hiding in open chat groups,

779
00:42:10,280 --> 00:42:13,600
money-sucking apps you sneak into with free Wi-Fi.

780
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:14,600
Filthy gym towels.

781
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:15,600
Huh?

782
00:42:15,600 --> 00:42:16,600
Full of germs, you know.

783
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:18,600
You...

784
00:42:18,600 --> 00:42:20,600
Ugh, enough, enough!

785
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:25,480
I admit it, we’re from Porn Airline.

786
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:27,320
But I could never bring myself to hurt Glamorous.

787
00:42:27,320 --> 00:42:28,320
I couldn’t hurt any of you.

788
00:42:34,040 --> 00:42:35,040
Oscar-worthy, huh?

789
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:37,240
I’ve got nothing left to prove.

790
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:40,360
Now, it’s up to all of you...

791
00:42:40,880 --> 00:42:42,400
do you still see us as friends?

792
00:42:42,520 --> 00:42:43,520
Nope.

793
00:42:43,760 --> 00:42:45,400
Nosy, you think you’re a flight attendant?

794
00:42:45,400 --> 00:42:48,120
Go fix lightbulbs or toilets or whatever...

795
00:42:48,120 --> 00:42:49,640
We did work for Madam Porn, yes.

796
00:42:50,520 --> 00:42:52,120
But we never intended to hurt you.

797
00:42:56,440 --> 00:42:58,440
But today, I intend to.

798
00:42:59,320 --> 00:43:02,080
